document.title: Button Component
document.description: Documentation for the Button component in ByteUI.

body.raw:
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button'; 
import { useState } from 'react';

# Button Component

The `Button` component is used to trigger an action or event. It supports various variants, sizes, and states.



## Usage

Hereâ€™s how you can use the `Button` component in your project:


<Button >Click Me</Button>
<Button variant="primary" onClick={() => alert('Primary Button Clicked')}>
  Primary Button
</Button>
<Button variant="secondary" onClick={() => alert('Secondary Button Clicked')}>
  Secondary Button
</Button>
<Button variant="destructive" onClick={() => alert('Danger Button Clicked')}>
  Danger Button
</Button>

```tsx
import { Button } from 'your-component-library';

<Button variant="primary">Click Me</Button>
